This article discusses an executive order issued by President Joe Biden to combat the COVID-19 pandemic in the United States. The order establishes the position of Coordinator of the COVID-19 Response and Counselor to the President, who will report directly to the President and coordinate all aspects of the COVID-19 response. The coordinator's duties include reducing disparities in the response, coordinating the production and distribution of supplies, expanding testing, supporting vaccine delivery, and ensuring the safe reopening of schools. The order also emphasizes global health security and biodefense, with the establishment of a National Security Council Principals Committee and an NSC Directorate on Global Health Security and Biodefense. The order directs agencies to bring any obstacles to the attention of the COVID-19 Response Coordinator, who will then inform the President. The order is subject to applicable law and availability of appropriations and does not create any enforceable rights or benefits.